GIF Viewer helper predecode path
================================

Date: 2026-07-02

Project
-------
Source cloned from:
https://git.code.sf.net/p/gifviewer/git

Local source:
source

Purpose
-------
Use the same bundled Pillow/PyInstaller helper created for Quivi as an optional
GIF predecode path for GIF Viewer.

The previous fast-scaling experiment was reverted because it did not improve
performance and made the quality selector appear ineffective during playback.
This change leaves CPictureBox/FormMain quality handling untouched and instead
changes GIFFile loading/playback internals.

Backups
-------
- backups/source-backups/GIFFile.cs.before-helper-predecode.20260702-023616.bak

Changed files
-------------
- source/GIFFile.cs
- tools/gifviewer_smoke_helper.ps1

Runtime files copied next to the test build
-------------------------------------------
- source/bin/Release/webp_extract_pillow_runtime/
- source/bin/Release/webp_extract_pillow.exe

Behavior
--------
- GIFFile.LoadFromPath first checks for:
  1. webp_extract_pillow_runtime/webp_extract_pillow/webp_extract_pillow.exe
  2. webp_extract_pillow.exe
- If found, it launches the helper hidden and asks it to decode the GIF to BMP
  frames plus delays.txt in a temp folder.
- BMP frames are cloned into 32bpp in-memory Bitmap objects.
- The temp folder is deleted after load.
- Frame playback copies pixels from the predecoded helper frames.
- If the helper is missing or fails, GIF Viewer falls back to its original
  GifDecoder path.
- CPictureBox quality selection is unchanged.

